#Sunrise Cafe Sales Datasets

A synthetic cafe sales dataset series built for practicing:
- Data Cleaning
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
- Dashboarding
- SQL Queries
- Data Visualization
- Handling Dirty Data

This project simulates the growth of a fictional cafe business called Sunrise Cafe from 2024–2026.

The datasets are intentionally designed with different corruption patterns and data quality issues to make them feel more realistic and useful for practice.

---

#Datasets

| Dataset | Rows | Description |
|---|---:|---|
| Dataset 1 | 10,000 | Early business stage, small operations, messy management |
| Dataset 2 | 50,000 | Rapid business growth, more staff, mixed data quality |
| Dataset 3 | 100,000 | Large-scale operations, higher transaction volume, more complex corruption |

---

#Columns

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| transaction_id | Unique transaction identifier |
| transaction_date | Transaction date |
| item | Purchased menu item |
| category | Item category |
| menu_id | Product identifier |
| qty | Quantity purchased |
| price | Price per item |
| total_spent | Total transaction value |
| payment method | Payment method used |
| order type | Dine in, take away, or online order |

---

#Intentional Data Issues

These datasets contain intentionally corrupted data such as:
- Missing values
- Invalid text values
- Inconsistent entries
- Corrupted categorical data
- Broken transaction records

Example error flags:
```text
error
unknown
missing

#Project Goals

The goal of this project is to create datasets that feel closer to real business data instead of perfectly clean tutorial datasets.

This repository is mainly built for:

    -Students
    -Beginner data analysts
    -Data cleaning practice
    -Portfolio projects
    -Dashboard testing

#Tools used

    -Python
    -Pandas
    -NumPy

##########-NOTES-##########
These datasets are fully synthetic and generated for educational purposes only.
No real customer or business data is used.
